2-Write a program that computes the days from the given day in common era to today. Your program should return integer or float with negative values representing the days in the future

Your program should compute the days after 1582 October 15 according to the Gregorian calendar and before 1582 October 4 according to the Julian calendar.
Your program should compute leap years correctly.
Your program may return number of days in integer or in float types.
Your program should raise and exception when the given date is invalid i.e. 29 February in non leap years or dates between October 5-14 in 1582.
For dates before common era, i.e before Christ it is up to you to implement the dates as in Julian calendar or simply raise a `NotImplementedException` exception.